 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has promised to take action against Police Minister Bheki Cele and National Commissioner Khehla Sitole. Earlier this week, in the State of the Nation debate, Cele claimed Sitole was plotting with EFF leader Julius Malema to remove him from office. READ: Police Instability | Sitole refutes Cele's allegations Sitole hit back, saying this isn't true. The president has not indicated when he'll deal with the matter. 